t reserves. It is likely that these insects use optic flow to gauge their speed and drift, and thus must migrate where sufficient detail in the Earth's surface is visible to them. The abilities of butterflies and dragonflies to adjust their airspeed over water indicate sophisticated control and guidance systems pertaining to migration.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Srygley, R. B.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Dudley, R.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/64be6293b9852f57046373560901ecc3", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/c680cd3dd798a1097b7fa677196f328f2f6321983e3972c082667c7a4c42a685", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/8WS67CKR", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/8WS67CKR", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/bdf288b6da9f890efcbf4e2a74e385a6!/b83370-85863", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "1", "pages": "119-133", "title": "Integrative and Comparative Biology", "volume": "48"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/64be6293b9852f57046373560901ecc3"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:8WS67CKR"}, {"identifier": "10.1093/icb/icn011"}], "communities": [{"id": "batlit"}, {"id"